# Errors

**Registry:** all codes in `features/common/errors/service-error.codes.ts`. New throwable error → add code + thin `ServiceError` subclass in feature `errors/`.

**Service errors:** `ServiceError` + stable `code` string. **Never** attach HTTP status to service-layer errors.

**HTTP mapping:** only in `plugins/fsre-error-handler.ts`. Add a map entry **only** if the code can reach the API. Codes without mapping (`fcm_send_message_failed`, `email_send_message_failed`, etc.) are internal/background-only.

**Routes:** rely on shared `onError` in `app.ts` — no per-route `instanceof` chains. Map by `error.code`, not per-class.

**FsreError** (`lib/errors.ts`) = legacy JSON response shape until RFC 9457 / Elysia 2.0 `problem()`.

```typescript
// ✅ repo boundary
catch (error) {
  throw new TimetableFetchFailed("...", error);
}

// ❌ in service
set.status = 502;
```
